#
#  Root options (run mode):
#    --cert <PATH>                  Path to root CA certificate
#                                   (creates file if absent;
#                                   default: ~/.hetty/hetty_cert.pem)
#    --key <PATH>                   Path to root CA private key
#                                   (creates if absent; default:
#                                   ~/.hetty/hetty_key.pem)
#    --db <PATH>                    Database file path (bbolt KV
#                                   store; creates if absent;
#                                   default: ~/.hetty/hetty.db)
#    --addr <HOST:PORT>             TCP address to listen on
#                                   (default: :8080)
#    --chrome                       Launch Chrome with proxy
#                                   settings applied and
#                                   certificate errors ignored
#                                   (default: false)
#    --verbose                      Enable verbose logging
#    --json                         Encode logs as JSON (instead
#                                   of pretty/human-readable)
#    --version, -v                  Output version
#    --help, -h                     Output usage text
#
#  Subcommand: cert
#    Certificate management for trust-store integration.
#    Run `hetty cert <subcommand> --help` for subcommand details.
#
#    cert install                   Install certificate to system
#                                   trust store (optionally Firefox/
#                                   Java)
#    cert uninstall                 Uninstall certificate from
#                                   trust stores
#
#    cert install/uninstall options:
#      --cert <PATH>                Path to certificate (default:
#                                   ~/.hetty/hetty_cert.pem)
#      --firefox                    Install/uninstall to/from Firefox
#                                   trust store (default: false)
#      --java                       Install/uninstall to/from Java
#                                   trust store (default: false)
#      --skip-system                Skip installing/uninstalling to/
#                                   from system trust store (default:
#                                   false)
#      --help, -h                   Output subcommand usage
#
#  Examples:
#    hetty                                              # Run with defaults (listen on :8080)
#    hetty --addr :8443                                 # Custom listen port
#    hetty --chrome                                     # Launch Chrome with proxy preconfigured
#    hetty --verbose --json                             # Verbose JSON logging
#    hetty --db /tmp/test.db --cert /tmp/ca.pem         # Custom paths
#    hetty cert install                                 # Install CA cert to system trust store
#    hetty cert install --firefox                       # Also install to Firefox
#    hetty cert install --firefox --java                # Install to Firefox + Java too
#    hetty cert install --skip-system --firefox         # Firefox only (skip system)
#    hetty cert uninstall                               # Uninstall CA cert from system
#    hetty cert uninstall --firefox --java              # Uninstall from all
#    hetty --version
#    hetty --help
#
